<br>
Right now the way characters are saved there is no way to record what buffs are on the pet.  The only reason our pets zone with us is because they are an icon in our buff window, thus the existance of the pet is saved with our character file.<br>
<br>
The buffs on the pet are NOT saved in our character file, which is why they are lost when you zone or go LD.  In order to keep the buffs, they would have to re-code the way characters are saved.<br>
<br>
The situation is even more dire for the other pet classes, because since their pet is NOT an icon in their buff window, even the existance of the pet itself is not saved in the character file, much less any buffs the pet may have.<br>
<br>
I'm sure it's something they would like to fix... pets being destroyed when your connection goes down is probably not something they had planned from the start.  Other things have taken a priority over their programming time, though.<br>
<br>
I've heard, however, that along with the new user interface they are also implementing a new format for saved characters.  That may fix this very problem.  We'll have to wait and see. <p><BR>
