<br>
It is already easy on a bad pull to get your pet to agro everything and give you enough time to run a little ways away and camp out.  This is tempored by the fact that once you get back in, you will have to rebuff your pet.  As long as your pet can last 30 seconds, there is no chance of you dieing and losing exp.<br>
<br>
Now, if you make it so your pet doesn't lose buffs, then there is no penalty to camping out.  No exp lose, no mana lose, time loss of less than a minute.<br>
<br>
I know you are talking about going LD and not camping or /q out of the game, but certain people can and will use every little thing in the game to maximize their experience without regard to how things were supposed to be used.  This is the main reason Verant has to do some things that make it rough on the rest of us.<br>
<br>
It is because of the possibility for exploitation that I do not expect Verant to ever make a change to this.<br>
<br>
