<br>
It would be very difficult for the game server to know when someone truly went LD through no fault of their own and when they did it on purpose.  And nothing I can think of that might help, would be 100% effective.<br>
<br>
For example, when connected the server pings you and finds out you are 10 hops away.  On a LD, the server pings you again and can only get 9 hops.  Does this mean that you turned your computer off?  Does this mean that you unplugged your router?  Or does this mean that the cable running to your house suddenly decided to quit working?  The first two are not valid LDs, but the last one is.  But how would the server be able to tell that?<br>
